-- National Bank Promotes Mulroney; BofA Moves Giroux, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-07-26T18:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-26/national-bank-promotes-mulroney-bofa-moves-giroux-vlaad-says.html
  National Bank of Canada (NA)  moved Mark Mulroney to head of  equity capital markets  from his former post
as co-head of institutional equity trading, according to Vlaad &
Co., a Toronto-based financial services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  * National Bank’s Frederic Girard became head of institutional
equity trading and Susan Monteith moved from head of equity
capital markets to executive vice president and managing
director of client strategy.  * In  Montreal , Euro Pacific Canada Inc. added Pierre-Yves Terrisse as vice president, institutional sales and Richard Ouellette as vice president, trading.  * Bank of America Merrill Lynch Canada appointed Eric Giroux as
head of the financial institutions, infrastructure and
government groups, replacing Marianne Harris, who is retiring.
Replacing Giroux as head of debt capital markets for  Canada  is
Jamie Hancock.  * Deutsche Bank hired Sean Urie for the equity sales team from
Citigroup Global Markets.  * Roynat Capital added Avinash D’Souza as an associate. He was
previously senior vice president at Rasmala Investments in
Dubai.  * Stonecap Securities hired Julie Paulson as a research
associate from Fraser Mackenzie.  To contact the reporter on this story:
